                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00111A Combat Areas/6: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sterling</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-11-08T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 8, 1939—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>78. Your 190, November 8, 2 p.m. By Proclamation of the President of November 4
                    defining combat areas American vessels cannot proceed to any port in Norway
                    south of Bergen; nor to any ports in Sweden, Denmark, nor to Baltic ports.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
